After an initial round of model fitting, models with convergence errors were subject to an outlier removal method. 10,000 simulated residuals were generated from the fitted models, and observed residuals were compared to simulated residuals using the DHARMa R package. Observed residuals that were outside the 2.5th and 97.5th percentiles of simulated residuals were considered outliers. These values were removed from the model training data, and models were refit to the reduced dataset. Outlier values were excluded from model fitting, but included in final evaluations.


This section contains all the R code to reproduce the current results and analysis.

